    "In 1990 Archer-Straw published <em>Jamaican Art</em>, the first book of its kind.": [],
    "The book was co-authored with editor-in-chief of <em>Jamaica Journal</em> and <em>Caribbean Quarterly</em> Kim Robinson-Walcott (b.": [],
    "1956), in addition to a foreword by curator of the National Gallery of Jamaica, David Boxer (b.": [],
    "1946).": [],
    "She chronicled for the first time the evolution of Jamaican art, highlighting key artists in the nation\u2019s history, like well-known sculptor Edna Manley (1900-1987), but also David Pottinger (1911-2007), Cecil Baugh (1908-2005), and Carl Abrahams (1913-2005).": [
